cat=106&_nc_ohc=iqYjZvOx36QAX8XUeHR&oh=5de6007834f41561fac3d02e2e385b03&oe=5F7D24FF";}i:21;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:22;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:2322378424;}i:23;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:24;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:25;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:26;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2390980873253222915";}i:27;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEueG-vAvoD";}i:28;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599247152;}i:29;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:1882:"Negative self-talk will “TALK” you out of your goals 

This is so true! Listen up! 

“Those who think they can and those who think they can’t are both usually right.” -Confucius

Here’s one exercise I use on my clients just starting out that shows their current mindset.

I will ask: 

💁🏻‍♂️ “What are your wins for the week?”

🙍🏻‍♀️Them: “Well this week wasn’t so good or I didn’t do this workout, I had a bad day of eating 

🤷🏻‍♂️Me: “ So those are your wins?”

🤷🏻‍♀️Them: “I had no wins really.” 

🙋🏻‍♂️Me: “ Looks like you exercised most of the week.”
Before you never exercised this many days in a week.”

🙋🏻‍♀️Them: “ I guess you’re right!.” 

80% of people who struggle with inconsistent exercise, yo yo dieting and self sabotage have all one thing in common.

❌NEGATIVE MINDSET❌

The reason is because you have not known success in a long time.

So you see patterns come up that made you quit or feel frustrated.

It’s easy to point out those patterns

BUT 

When you start to point out the GOOD, we can amplify our results and focus on action steps toward what we need to approve 

You have two choices. 

1️⃣Feel like you’ve failed this week 

OR 

2️⃣Celebrate the small wins and take the action steps needed for true change 

That’s what we teach at the next level fitness academy 

Not only body transformation, but mindset transformation ✅

If you have reached this point and resonate with this post 

Message me or comment “I’M IN” 

For a free complimentary coaching call to get crystal clear on your health and fitness goals

