How To improve Metabolic Flexibility (Fat & Carbohydrate Metabolism)

This could be achieved by changes in diet, like the one I'm following and lots of my client's - carb cycling or switching from a high carb to low carb diet. 

Low carb days decrease the insulin spike, thus improving insulin sensitivity, and deplete your body's carb stores, enhancing mitochondrial function. 

A high-functioning mitochondrial density enables burning more fat for energy.

High carb days ensure your body's ability to use carbs for energy and keep hormones in balance.

